    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-05-10T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-05-10T18:00:00-05:00" n="786"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d786">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">892.014/5–1046: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Caffery</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-05-10T19:00:00-04:00"
                            >May 10, 1946—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2257. <gloss target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> 2231, May 10.<note n="52"
                        xml:id="d786fn1">Not printed; it summarized the oral communication handed to
                        the French Minister on May 9, <ref target="#pg_994">p. 994</ref>.</note>
                    Further <gloss target="#t_Info1">info</gloss> reported French attack Nakorn
                    Phanom received (<gloss target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> 2230, May 10<note
                        n="53" xml:id="d786fn2">Not printed; it quoted telegram 496, May 8, 10 p.m.,
                        from Bangkok, <ref target="#pg_993">p. 993</ref>.</note>). This area remote
                    from any disputed territory.</p>
                <p>You are requested in your discretion make representations <gloss
                        target="#t_FonOff1">FonOff</gloss> expressing concern US Govt and hope
                    French Govt will act immediately to take all necessary steps prevent further
                    such incidents which involve danger additional bloodshed and can only make more
                    difficult satisfactory Franco-Siamese settlement and restoration friendly
                    relations.</p>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss> understands Brit Ambassador<note n="54"
                        xml:id="d786fn3">Alfred Duff Cooper.</note> has made similar
                    representations, and you may wish to ascertain steps he has taken prior to
                    acting.</p>
                <p>Sent Paris. Repeated Bangkok, London, Saigon.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
